Dwarf: {
	QuestName: Stolen memories
	QuestDescription: Somewhere deep within the frozen reaches of the winter biome lies an ancient Dwarven Anvil, half-buried beneath layers of ice and time. Forged in an age when dwarven forges still burned bright beneath the mountains, it hums faintly with forgotten power.
	QuestStage: Collect Dwarven Anvil
	QuestProgress0: Thanks for the Anvil!
	QuestProgress1:
		'''
		Previously, the dwarves were digging in the mines in 
		search of precious Valhallite ore. They were constantly 
		dragging giant anvils that stayed there forever, 
		could you bring me one? And I'll give you some ore
		'''
	QuestProgress2: I know it's kinda hard to find but if you do I would be incredibly grateful!
	QuestButton: Accept
	QuestButtonGive: Give away
	QuestCompleted:
		'''
		I can't believe that i see it again.. My father used it last 
		time when he was alive.. Nevermind, there's a reward.
		'''
	QuestCompletedFalse: You don't have an anvil yet.
}

Hunter: {
	QuestName: Whispering Reed
	QuestDescription: In the damp stillness of the swamps grows a peculiar plant known as the Whispering Reed. Its thin stalks sway even when the air is unmoving, as if stirred by voices no one else can hear. Travelers often speak of faint murmurs echoing through the marsh at dusk. Secrets carried by the reeds themselves. Some believe they are remnants of lost souls, others say it is simply the swamplings lurking.
	QuestStage: Collect Whispering Reed
	QuestProgress0: Thanks for it, you are doing great things!
	QuestProgress1: I heard stories about the swamps. They say something down there sings when the moon is high. Bring me a Whispering Reed, if you dare.
	QuestProgress2: Still searching, huh? Swamps don't give up their secrets easily. Listen for the hum thats how you'll know you're close.
	QuestButton: Accept
	QuestButtonGive: Give away a Whispering Reed
	QuestCompleted: So you found it, a Whispering Reed. You can almost hear their voices, can't you? Keep it close - it remembers those who listen.
	QuestCompletedFalse: You don't have a Whispering Reed.
}

Artist: {
	QuestName: Red Husk.
	QuestDescription: Red Husk grows quietly in the depths of the caves, clinging to stone where little else survives. Its dry and crimson shell feels fragile, almost like it could crumble at a touch. It doesn’t seem fully dead, but not alive either, just something left behind. Miners tend to ignore it, aldthough some say it appears more often in places where the air feels heavier than usual.
	QuestStage: Collect Red Husk.
	QuestProgress0: I'm really grateful for the Red Husk!
	QuestProgress1: Have you ever seen the color that bleeds between dusk and fire? They call it Red Husk. I need it - no, I ache for it. Bring me that hue from the deep caves.
	QuestProgress2: The canvas waits… empty. The color haunts my dreams. Did you find it? The Red Husk? Faster
	QuestButton: Accept
	QuestButtonGive: Give a husk
	QuestCompleted: Look at it - that living crimson! With this, my painting will finally breathe. You've given me more than pigment… you've given me a heartbeat.
	QuestCompletedFalse: You don't have a Red Husk.
}

Ninja: {
	QuestName: Carrot
	QuestDescription: A simple carrot. Bright, crisp, and reliable. Not much to look at, but always useful when you need it.
	QuestStage: Collect Carrot.
	QuestProgress0: Thanks for the Carrot!
	QuestProgress1: After long durance i need… a carrot. Sounds stupid? Maybe. But that holds power for my arms- and I want it.
	QuestProgress2: Still empty-handed? Hmph. The bunny's tricks are slippery, but not as slippery as excuses.
	QuestButton: Accept
	QuestButtonGive: Give Carrot
	QuestCompleted: Power hidden in a vegetable - perfect disguise. You did well, shadow friend.
	QuestCompletedFalse: You don't have a Carrot.
}

